cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with games played over word-generating higher-order recursion schemes, which are closely related to logical systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses program synthesis in the context of two-player games. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with regular languages and finite automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes an algorithm for the analysis of two-player inclusion games. 
- cs.LT (Computational Linguistics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with word-generating recursion schemes and regular languages, which are relevant to natural language processing.
